description.narrative: Intermediate Results (IR) 3: Health policies, strategies and systems supportive of Maternal, Neonatal, and Child Health (MNCH) scale-up and mitigation of emergencies., which contributes to Adolescent Empowerment, Care And Treatment Of Children Affected By Hiv And Aids, Child Health, Community-Based Management Of Acute Malnutrition, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Health Systems Strengthening, Hygiene, Immunization, Infant And Young Child Feeding, Maternal And Newborn Health, Micronutrients, Operations Support To Programme Delivery, Polio Eradication, Sanitation. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: UNICEF will contribute to increasing number of women and children have equitable Access to and Use of Quality Essential Social and Protection Services and practices with fon vulnerable groups and the most marginalised regions of Kenya by 2013
